WEBVTT

00:04.404 --> 00:05.928
Hi, Kerry.

00:06.606 --> 00:09.097
- Oh, hi, Jason.
- Hi, Mrs. Hennessy.

00:09.175 --> 00:12.838
Well... Kerry?

00:17.217 --> 00:19.583
So I thought
you and Jason broke it off.

00:19.686 --> 00:23.053
We did, but Mr. Reynolds teamed us up
to work on this history project.

00:23.123 --> 00:26.559
Ah... So I guess "on-again, off-again"
is on again.

00:28.094 --> 00:29.186
Sounds like fate.

00:29.262 --> 00:32.095
Sounds like his name
follows mine alphabetically.

00:32.966 --> 00:34.524
But we'll see.

00:35.268 --> 00:37.236
- What's that?
- Mount Vesuvius.

00:37.303 --> 00:39.328
We're trying to show how its eruption

00:39.406 --> 00:43.240
helped preserve the Pompeian culture
for future generations to study.

00:45.045 --> 00:47.570
You know what? You could
melt some of my army men

00:47.647 --> 00:49.615
to look like the slower villagers.

00:52.452 --> 00:53.510
I like it.

00:54.120 --> 00:57.089
You're in luck. I was just
going upstairs to melt some.

00:58.858 --> 01:01.622
You know, if the FBI
is looking through our trash,

01:01.728 --> 01:03.195
he'll be the reason.

01:03.897 --> 01:05.865
That's funny, Mrs. Hennessy.

01:07.600 --> 01:09.067
Well, thanks, Jason.

01:11.805 --> 01:14.968
I like your mom.
She's nice, pretty, smart.

01:15.608 --> 01:17.075
What did you say?

01:18.878 --> 01:22.837
Um... Your mom was nice and smart.

01:23.750 --> 01:27.117
And pretty.
You said my mom was pretty.

01:27.220 --> 01:29.780
You never said I was pretty
when we were dating.

01:31.291 --> 01:33.259
I thought it was implied.

01:34.561 --> 01:36.927
Because you are, real pretty.

01:37.030 --> 01:39.362
- As pretty as my mom?
- Well, yeah.

01:39.432 --> 01:40.729
Wrong answer!

01:41.901 --> 01:44.802
So what, you're gonna say
my mom is pretty and then leave?

01:44.871 --> 01:46.771
Yeah.

01:46.840 --> 01:49.172
Hey, Care Bear, seems like old times.

01:49.242 --> 01:51.369
I come into a room, Jason runs out.

01:51.444 --> 01:53.605
- Yeah.
- Don't you look pretty today?

01:53.680 --> 01:55.011
Stay out of my life.

01:56.116 --> 01:57.777
Yeah, seems like old times.

01:59.000 --> 02:05.074
